{{Quote|Anakin, the Kashirim are ''notorious'' throughout the galaxy for one thing: ''stealing''. A competent thief is considered a great value to their society. They are judged socially by their ability to pilfer.|Obi-Wan Kenobi, to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]]|<ref name="JedisWeapon">{{StoryCite|story=A Jedi's Weapon|book=Free Comic Book Day 2002 Special|manual=1}}</ref>}}
[[File:ShaMarMaDredAndHisWives-AJedisWeapon.jpg|thumb|right|250px|The Kashirim King Sha-Mar Ma-dred of Kashir (top left) and his wives traveled to Coruscant to meet with the Jedi (bottom, from left to right) Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker.]]
The '''Kashirim''' were the native people of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kashir]]. The group included [[Human/Legends|Humans]].<ref name="JedisWeapon" />

According to [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], Kashirim were known throughout the [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]] as thieves and pick-pockets, since stealing was an honored tradition and practiced art at Kashir.

